have been swept up

18:58.771 --> 19:02.006
by an invisible force.

19:02.041 --> 19:04.642
And now they speak
what they believe is the

19:04.677 --> 19:06.878
language of heaven.

19:06.913 --> 19:09.413
I can see on their
faces that they are

19:09.449 --> 19:13.885
genuinely somewhere else.

19:22.795 --> 19:27.165
You were there for a long time.

19:27.200 --> 19:30.535
You don't have any idea
what you were saying?

19:30.570 --> 19:33.538
No, but when you
let the Holy Spirit flow

19:33.573 --> 19:39.810
through you, then, I mean,
then you don't have any control

19:40.013 --> 19:42.180
over yourself and it's
just the Holy Spirit,

19:42.215 --> 19:44.115
The Holy Spirit
speaking to you,

19:44.150 --> 19:45.683
And I can't wait
till I go to heaven,

19:45.718 --> 19:48.419
because that's how
I will be at all times.

19:48.454 --> 19:50.121
Well, you know,

19:50.156 --> 19:52.690
I've been going to the
cultural experiences of

19:52.725 --> 19:55.726
different religions
and belief systems,

19:55.762 --> 19:59.530
and the thing that I have
learned is that everybody's

19:59.566 --> 20:03.434
truth is the truth.

20:10.710 --> 20:13.844
That was quite a
powerful experience.

20:13.880 --> 20:16.480
I could...

20:16.516 --> 20:22.386
feel the energy in that space.

20:22.422 --> 20:28.859
Normal people suddenly
transformed by some power.

20:29.495 --> 20:34.932
And then just as suddenly
return to normal.

20:34.968 --> 20:38.869
Pentecostals believe that
they are bringing heaven down to

20:38.905 --> 20:44.075
earth, now, whatever it is,
once they felt that power

20:44.110 --> 20:46.210
they're not the same.

20:46.246 --> 20:51.282
Experience changes them.

20:51.317 --> 20:56.654
How they see themselves,
how they relate to others...

20:58.958 --> 21:03.494
how they live their lives.

21:04.130 --> 21:06.897
The Pentecostals feel the
presence of heaven through

21:06.933 --> 21:09.634
their unique ritual.

21:09.669 --> 21:14.171
But one Hindu king physically
built heaven on earth.

21:14.207 --> 21:17.908
To entice the gods
to reside in there.

21:23.449 --> 21:27.251
Mississippi is my home.

21:27.287 --> 21:30.321
Being here just feels...

21:30.356 --> 21:32.590
right.

21:32.625 --> 21:36.160
To me it's like heaven on earth.

21:36.195 --> 21:41.699
And we all yearn for that
place where you're at ease,

21:41.734 --> 21:45.269
the place where you
feel you belong.

21:45.305 --> 21:49.206
The ancient Jews sought
the heaven of their homeland

21:49.242 --> 21:52.476
when they left Babylon.

21:52.512 --> 21:57.815
The Mormons found theirs
by the Great Salt Lake.

21:57.850 --> 22:03.487
It's a universal human
urge to find your heaven

22:03.523 --> 22:07.158
here, and now.

22:15.301 --> 22:21.072
In the jungles of Cambodia,
over 900 years ago,

22:21.107 --> 22:25.409
one king built his
own heaven on earth.

22:30.583 --> 22:35.219
This is Angkor Wat.

22:36.856 --> 22:41.625
It's the largest religious
monument in the world.

22:42.595 --> 22:45.162
Today it's a Buddhist temple,

22:45.198 --> 22:48.466
but that wasn't
always the case.

22:48.501 --> 22:51.502
It was originally
constructed by the king of

22:51.537 --> 22:54.772
the Khmer empire,
Suryavarman II,

22:54.807 --> 22:58.609
as a model of Hindu heaven.

23:08.287 --> 23:11.055
Hey David, how are you?

23:12.458 --> 23:13.657
It's been a while.

23:13.693 --> 23:14.925
Right.

23:14.961 --> 23:16.160
Welcome, welcome.

23:16.195 --> 23:17.962
Thank you, Thank you, very much.

23:17.997 --> 23:20.431
Archaeologist, David Brotherson,

23:20.466 --> 23:22.099
as enlisted the aid of
Cambodian historian,

23:22.135 --> 23:25.269
Syan Superovi to understand
why this incredible

23:25.304 --> 23:26.937
site was built.

23:26.973 --> 23:29.273
It’s mind boggling how much work

23:29.308 --> 23:31.942
was put into building this
immaculate building.

23:31.978 --> 23:33.277
Tremendously.

23:33.312 --> 23:35.646
And the amount of manpower that was

23:35.681 --> 23:38.883
deployed here, there must
have been a very important

23:38.918 --> 23:41.619
underlying reason for them
to go to all this effort?

23:41.654 --> 23:45.022
Definitely.

23:45.491 --> 23:48.626
This whole complex
itself is the symbolisms of

23:48.661 --> 23:50.895
the entire universe.

23:50.930 --> 23:54.865
Moat, in the Hindu mythology,
Moat is symbolizing the oceans

23:54.901 --> 23:58.936
that is surrounding
Mount Meru.

23:59.439 --> 24:01.305
In Hindu mythology,

24:01.340 --> 24:03.941
the five peaks of
Mount Meru are the center

24:03.976 --> 24:05.810
of the universe.

24:05.845 --> 24:09.246
The heavenly abode of the gods.

24:11.417 --> 24:13.517
So, the Moats which surround these

24:13.553 --> 24:17.955
temples are huge, and they
symbolize the ocean that

24:17.990 --> 24:20.958
surrounds where the gods live.

24:20.993 --> 24:23.494
The entire complex itself
symbolizing the

24:23.529 --> 24:24.929
universe, right?

24:24.964 --> 24:27.531
But, this temple, it's not only that,

24:27.567 --> 24:31.368
it is the heaven on earth,
it is the place called the

24:31.404 --> 24:35.306
highest world of Vishnu,
in Sanskrit it's called...

24:37.710 --> 24:39.410
I believe
I read the translation,

24:39.445 --> 24:43.514
It's a sacred paradise
of Vishnu as well.

24:43.549 --> 24:46.016
The Hindu god, Vishnu,

24:46.052 --> 24:48.919
Is the protector of
creation and Angkor Wat was

24:48.955 --> 24:50.855
built for him.

24:50.890 --> 24:53.524
Inside the temple are
over 12,000 square feet of

24:53.559 --> 24:56.760
intricately carved reliefs.

24:56.796 --> 25:00.164
One relief was created
to link king Suryavarman II

25:00.199 --> 25:04.301
to Vishnu himself.

25:05.738 --> 25:08.606
Look, you can see that by relief,

25:08.641 --> 25:10.708
the king who build this temple,

25:10.743 --> 25:12.943
and if you look
closely over there,

25:12.979 --> 25:14.745
there is an
inscription saying...

25:19.585 --> 25:23.988
Meaning that he is the king
who went through the highest

25:24.023 --> 25:28.058
world of Vishnu.

25:30.496 --> 25:32.830
Archaeologists
aren't sure whether

25:32.865 --> 25:35.599
the king is buried here,
but local people believe that

25:35.635 --> 25:40.471
his spirit resides here
in Vishnu’s paradise.

25:40.606 --> 25:43.140
That paradise, that heaven,

25:43.175 --> 25:47.278
lies at the top
of the central tower.

25:47.613 --> 25:50.414
So they believe that Suryavarman II's

25:50.449 --> 25:53.684
spirit would inhabit these
towers in the afterlife?

25:53.719 --> 25:55.886
Exactly, exactly, exactly.

25:55.922 --> 25:58.856
If you look at the steps, you
know, like the wider the step,

25:58.891 --> 26:03.727
why it's too narrow, you know,
like it can be implied the

26:03.763 --> 26:06.730
ideas of that you are
approaching the worlds of god

26:06.766 --> 26:10.067
is not that easy.

26:10.937 --> 26:12.503
Alright, well,

26:12.538 --> 26:14.338
let's not wait a moment
longer, let's go up.

26:14.373 --> 26:18.008
Please come.

26:30.523 --> 26:32.957
The peak of the temple
was believed by the

26:32.992 --> 26:36.093
khmer to be the highest
reaches of heaven and the

26:36.128 --> 26:39.430
realm of Vishnu himself.

26:47.440 --> 26:49.239
David, what do you think?

26:49.275 --> 26:51.642
I think that everyone is impressed

26:51.677 --> 26:53.110
by your ancestors.

26:53.145 --> 26:54.511
Yeah, yeah.

26:54.547 --> 26:56.647
This is phenomenal.

26:56.682 --> 26:59.516
Perhaps they were
building such immaculate,

26:59.552 --> 27:02.586
beautiful structures
to entice the gods to inhabit

27:02.622 --> 27:05.990
these structures so that
the priests, the king,

27:06.025 --> 27:09.159
would have had this
opportunity to have a direct

27:09.195 --> 27:12.262
connection with the supernatural.

27:12.298 --> 27:13.797
That’s true.

27:13.833 --> 27:16.533
Even if you're not a spiritual person

27:16.569 --> 27:20.004
you can feel the aura of
this kind of place, you know,

27:20.039 --> 27:23.907
we really are
at heaven on earth.

27:27.413 --> 27:30.414
Angkor Wat is
an impressive example of

27:30.449 --> 27:35.319
one man's attempt to
build a heaven on earth, but,

27:35.354 --> 27:39.990
I wonder does it have
to be so monumental?

27:40.026 --> 27:43.394
So elaborate?

27:44.363 --> 27:48.365
2,000 years ago,
in Galilee and Jerusalem,

27:48.401 --> 27:52.236
a man called Jesus
began his ministry.

27:52.271 --> 27:55.305
He told his followers
that they would inherit the

27:55.341 --> 27:58.509
kingdom of heaven.

27:58.544 --> 28:00.444
I've always struggled to
understand what he meant

28:00.479 --> 28:04.982
by that, whether the
heaven he spoke of was

28:05.017 --> 28:08.619
up in the sky or down
here on earth.

28:19.165 --> 28:21.598
There's one group of
Christians that might know the

28:21.634 --> 28:24.201
answer to that question.

28:24.236 --> 28:27.404
The Assyrian Christian church
dates its foundation to just a

28:27.440 --> 28:30.607
few years after Jesus’s death.

28:30.643 --> 28:36.013
It claims its theology is
what Jesus himself believed.

28:36.182 --> 28:39.616
For them, heaven means
being close to god,

28:39.652 --> 28:43.987
hell is being far from god.

28:44.023 --> 28:48.425
The Assyrian community's
home is now called Iraq.

28:53.566 --> 28:56.567
So, I wanted to understand
how you can find a piece of

28:56.602 --> 29:01.805
heaven when you are living
in what became hell on earth?

29:12.752 --> 29:14.785
I've been invited
to break bread with two

29:14.820 --> 29:19.156
Assyrians from Baghdad.

29:20.960 --> 29:22.226
Hi, how are you sir?

29:22.261 --> 29:23.761
Just fine, how are you?

29:23.796 --> 29:25.496
Mervat Schlyaman...

29:25.531 --> 29:26.930
Nice to see you.

29:26.966 --> 29:28.766
And her son, Mattius Aneuam.

29:28.801 --> 29:31.101
Hi, my name's Mattius.

29:31.137 --> 29:32.236
Mattius.

29:32.271 --> 29:34.671
Nice to meet you, have a seat.

29:34.707 --> 29:36.607
Would you like some tea?

29:36.642 --> 29:40.410
Thank you, that would be nice.

29:41.580 --> 29:43.180
Ah.

29:43.783 --> 29:45.449
You're from Iraq?

29:45.484 --> 29:47.117
Uh huh, yes.

29:47.153 --> 29:48.886
But you're not Iraqi?

29:48.921 --> 29:50.888
You are?

29:50.923 --> 29:52.556
We’re Assyrian Christians,

29:52.591 --> 29:54.625
we lived in Iraq
for over 2,000 years.

29:54.660 --> 29:55.993
How old are you?

29:56.028 --> 29:58.762
I'm just kidding.

29:58.964 --> 30:01.231
But the Assyrian Christians
have been there since

30:01.267 --> 30:03.033
the time of Jesus?

30:04.570 --> 30:09.173
You were in Iraq and then the

30:09.208 --> 30:11.341
civil war broke out?

30:11.377 --> 30:13.110
Yes.

30:13.145 --> 30:15.946
That's the insurgence against

30:15.981 --> 30:17.447
the government?

30:18.984 --> 30:20.217
And you were still there?

30:20.252 --> 30:21.518
Yes.

30:21.554 --> 30:22.886
During the war?

30:22.922 --> 30:24.454
Must have been awful.

30:31.230 --> 30:34.464
She’s saying,
before the war started the

30:34.500 --> 30:36.567
Muslim and the Christian
community they were all

30:36.602 --> 30:39.336
peaceful, everyone was
treated equally, but,

30:39.371 --> 30:41.738
when the war started everything

30:41.774 --> 30:43.774
started going downhill.

30:52.151 --> 30:54.117
Is that problematical?

30:54.153 --> 30:56.186
That you were
Assyrian Christians in a

30:56.222 --> 30:59.089
largely Muslim country?

31:05.030 --> 31:07.164
There was no law and order between

31:07.199 --> 31:11.702
the communities, and
the militants thought that

31:11.737 --> 31:15.572
the Christians were working
with the American soldiers,

31:15.608 --> 31:19.509
so, started creating problems.

31:26.619 --> 31:28.719
The insurgents,

31:28.754 --> 31:31.021
they put bombs in cars and
they used to really to put 'em

31:31.056 --> 31:33.757
like in front of churches
and other religious areas and

31:33.792 --> 31:36.760
they'd blow 'em up.

31:40.199 --> 31:44.067
Didn’t that frighten you?

31:50.376 --> 31:53.176
She said, yeah, it frightened us.

31:53.212 --> 31:55.779
We hear like that
church got blown up,

31:55.814 --> 31:59.049
it struck fear in our hearts.

31:59.084 --> 32:00.617
We started getting threats.

32:00.653 --> 32:02.119
Threats?

32:02.154 --> 32:03.253
Yeah.

32:03.289 --> 32:04.655
What kind of threats?

32:04.690 --> 32:10.227
"We’re gonna Kidnap
your son and kill you."

32:10.496 --> 32:14.965
Wow, so then what?

32:15.301 --> 32:16.867
You left Baghdad?

32:16.902 --> 32:19.036
Yeah, we did leave.

32:19.071 --> 32:20.704
Where'd you go?

32:20.739 --> 32:24.241
We got onto a bus
with some of our

32:24.276 --> 32:27.711
clothes and we
just went to Syria.

32:27.880 --> 32:31.448
Out of the frying pan into the fire.

32:32.117 --> 32:35.719
Within a year of their
arrival in Syria,

32:35.754 --> 32:39.957
Marvat and Mattius faced
A new threat, ISIS.

32:44.530 --> 32:46.997
We actually Filed
applications with the

32:47.032 --> 32:50.367
United Nations and they
actually accepted us to come

32:50.402 --> 32:54.838
to the United States.

32:55.274 --> 32:57.140
Welcome to the U.S.

32:57.176 --> 32:58.875
Thank you.

32:58.911 --> 33:03.213
I want you to, for me,
to make a comparison.

33:03.248 --> 33:07.985
Your time in the hottest
part of Iraq and the hottest

33:08.020 --> 33:12.222
part of Syria,
and your life now?

33:14.159 --> 33:18.495
It's life here, freedom.

33:18.697 --> 33:21.365
Freedom of religion,

33:21.400 --> 33:24.034
it's really different to
come here, to America,

33:24.069 --> 33:28.305
I do think between the
heaven and hell and I compare

33:28.340 --> 33:31.608
it to my life.

33:32.644 --> 33:34.945
Mervan and
Mattius have joined other

33:34.980 --> 33:38.048
Assyrian refugees in
California's central valley,

33:38.083 --> 33:42.586
where they can live
and pray in peace.

33:44.857 --> 33:48.291
Mervat and Mattius have
lived through hell on earth,

33:48.327 --> 33:50.694
they were chased out of two
countries because of their

33:50.729 --> 33:55.065
faith, but, the promise of
heaven rooted in a tradition

33:55.100 --> 33:59.369
that goes back to the time of
Christ gave them the strength

33:59.405 --> 34:02.506
to find a better life,

34:02.541 --> 34:06.743
they made it to
their kingdom of heaven.

34:08.380 --> 34:10.781
Finding heaven on earth
is a goal for many faiths

34:10.815 --> 34:14.484
around the world.

34:14.520 --> 34:19.489
But in the jungles of Mexico,
the faithful dared to step

34:19.525 --> 34:22.159
into their own heaven.

34:22.194 --> 34:24.995
In an underwater graveyard.

34:32.304 --> 34:36.273
As a youngster
growing up in Mississippi,

34:36.308 --> 34:39.443
Hollywood seemed
impossibly far away.

34:39.478 --> 34:43.513
A land I only dreamed
of ever seeing.

34:43.549 --> 34:45.982
Many faithful think of
heaven the same way,

34:46.018 --> 34:49.085
an impossible realm that
you will never set foot in,

34:49.121 --> 34:51.621
in this life.

34:51.657 --> 34:57.360
Or is heaven a place where
you can come back from and

34:57.396 --> 34:59.863
tell the tale?

35:07.005 --> 35:10.373
In Mexico’s Yucatan peninsula
the ancient Maya believed they

35:10.409 --> 35:12.976
had found entry ways to
heaven through water filled,

35:13.011 --> 35:16.146
underground caverns.

35:17.449 --> 35:21.084
Called cenotes.

35:21.954 --> 35:24.387
Archaeologist and National
Geographic explorer,

35:24.423 --> 35:28.291
Giamo Dianda and his
colleague, Dante Garcia,

35:28.327 --> 35:31.094
are here to dive
at two cenotes deep in

35:31.130 --> 35:34.664
the Yucatan jungle.

35:36.101 --> 35:38.969
They are searching for
evidence that the Maya entered

35:39.004 --> 35:42.205
these cenotes to offer
human sacrifices to their

35:42.241 --> 35:45.475
god of rain, Chaac.

35:49.047 --> 35:50.147
What’s up?

35:50.182 --> 35:51.581
Good to see you again, man.

35:51.617 --> 35:53.116
Nice to see you again.

35:53.152 --> 35:55.252
Pedro Flores is a descendant of the

35:55.287 --> 35:58.488
ancient Maya people
who lived in this area.

36:01.360 --> 36:03.426
This is the cenote that I talked

36:03.462 --> 36:04.661
to you about.

36:04.696 --> 36:07.564
Oh this is great,
it's a great entrance.

36:07.599 --> 36:11.201
It’s very mystical for me,
the cenotes,

36:11.236 --> 36:16.873
with water, is the closest
doorway to underground heaven.

36:17.109 --> 36:19.843
This is the threshold
between our world,

36:19.878 --> 36:22.546
physical world, and
the spiritual world.

36:22.581 --> 36:26.683
And the world of gods
like for instance Chaac.

36:27.419 --> 36:29.586
Maya legend says the rain god,

36:29.621 --> 36:33.123
Chaac, lived in the
clouds, the heavens.

36:33.158 --> 36:36.326
But his heaven also extended
underground where Chaacs

36:36.361 --> 36:39.529
avatars scoop up water
from the cenotes with

36:39.565 --> 36:43.133
earthenware jars to make rain.

36:43.168 --> 36:46.836
Thunder is the sound of these
jars being broken open and

36:46.872 --> 36:50.840
releasing the downpour.
The rain was vital for the survival

36:50.876 --> 36:55.312
of the corn crop, and,
in turn, the Maya people.

36:55.714 --> 36:58.348
Archaeologists
believe ancient Maya

36:58.383 --> 37:01.885
would come to the cenotes and
offer human sacrifices to

37:01.920 --> 37:05.822
bring the rain.

37:11.797 --> 37:15.098
Before Giamo and Dante
Enter the cenote Pedro

37:15.133 --> 37:17.367
makes an offering to Chaac.

37:23.475 --> 37:27.077
I just asked permission you, Chaac,

37:27.112 --> 37:30.880
the father of rain,
father of water, thunders,

37:30.916 --> 37:35.051
he's the one who gonna
help us to go in safe and

37:35.087 --> 37:37.087
get back safe.

37:37.122 --> 37:40.790
Thank you.

37:41.994 --> 37:44.461
Go.

38:13.625 --> 38:15.992
Giamo and Dante dive 100 feet

38:16.028 --> 38:18.728
below the surface.

38:18.764 --> 38:21.931
They discover some carved
stones which Giamo believes

38:21.967 --> 38:27.771
could be over 1000 years old,
but no sign of human remains.

38:34.446 --> 38:37.647
Giamo hopes they will find
proof of human sacrifice at

38:37.683 --> 38:42.519
another cenote that's two
and a half miles away.

38:47.025 --> 38:51.628
So we rappel down
and suit up and make

38:51.663 --> 38:55.865
a quick look, we will forage.

38:56.034 --> 38:58.601
Access to the second cenote requires

38:58.637 --> 39:03.873
the divers to be lowered down
to the water 30 feet below.

39:16.621 --> 39:20.990
Giamo and Dante discover
some pottery, and then...

39:24.096 --> 39:29.532
the evidence of sacrifice
they've been looking for.

39:30.369 --> 39:32.402
This is the ultimate
offering you can

39:32.437 --> 39:36.272
make to gods, human blood
or a human life.

39:36.308 --> 39:40.243
So, in times of desperation,
big droughts, no rain,

39:40.278 --> 39:44.614
no agriculture, it's maybe
time to do a sacrifice and to

39:44.649 --> 39:47.984
appease the gods and to
ask for them, to beg them,

39:48.019 --> 39:51.020
to make rain.

39:51.056 --> 39:54.457
The ritual importance of
these places, cenotes and caves,

39:54.493 --> 39:57.594
they are strong, they have huge,

39:57.629 --> 40:02.365
important energies that
the Maya knew about,

40:02.401 --> 40:05.468
and these people
supposed to, sometimes,

40:05.504 --> 40:09.873
carry a message for the
gods that live there.

40:11.910 --> 40:14.377
The Maya believed cenotes were

40:14.413 --> 40:16.846
passageways to heaven,

40:16.882 --> 40:20.450
some who ventured into
those waters returned,

40:20.485 --> 40:22.852
I'm sure they
told incredible tales of

40:22.888 --> 40:26.623
what they saw.

40:29.227 --> 40:33.963
Across the world, in India,
Hindus also believe they have

40:33.999 --> 40:37.834
a passageway to an eternal
world, the Ganges river.

40:39.938 --> 40:45.341
It leads to a state of
pure energy called moksha.

40:45.744 --> 40:49.245
Hindus believe
in reincarnation,

40:49.281 --> 40:53.616
but when they reach moksha,
their version of heaven,

40:53.652 --> 40:56.419
they don't return to earth.

40:56.455 --> 40:59.956
We can't ask them any more
than we can ask the Maya what

40:59.991 --> 41:05.595
heaven is like, but, today,
thanks to modern medicine,

41:05.964 --> 41:10.066
people occasionally die
and come back to life.

41:10.101 --> 41:15.305
Perhaps they have tales
of heaven to tell us?

41:23.381 --> 41:27.016
To learn what heaven might
be like I’m going to speak

41:27.052 --> 41:31.354
to a woman who claims she
went there when she died.

41:31.590 --> 41:32.889
Would you like to come and sit?

41:32.924 --> 41:34.290
Surely.

41:34.326 --> 41:37.594
A physician's assistant
named Krista Gorman.

41:37.629 --> 41:42.131
You had a near
death experience,

41:42.634 --> 41:44.667
I'm talking to a real,

41:44.703 --> 41:47.370
live woman who had
a near death experience?

41:47.405 --> 41:50.206
Uh huh, yes you are.

41:50.242 --> 41:52.642
What led up to that?

41:52.677 --> 41:56.045
Well, I was pregnant
with my daughter and

41:56.081 --> 41:58.715
I went in a week before
she was due because she

41:58.750 --> 42:00.984
had a problem with her
kidney, not only that,

42:01.019 --> 42:05.255
but her heart rate
was dropping very low.

42:09.895 --> 42:12.862
So, they said, you know,
we need to do a C-section,

42:12.898 --> 42:16.633
and it was too
dangerous to wait.

42:21.506 --> 42:27.143
I started having trouble
breathing and I passed out.

42:38.690 --> 42:41.291
They lost my pulse
for eight minutes.

42:41.326 --> 42:43.793
Can we define that as death?

42:43.828 --> 42:47.730
In the clinical sense, perhaps.

42:47.766 --> 42:49.999
My heart stopped beating,
I wasn't getting any blood

42:50.035 --> 42:51.568
flow to my brain.

42:51.603 --> 42:55.138
Okay, so, you pass out.

42:55.307 --> 42:57.840
Then the next thing
I remember was being

42:57.876 --> 43:02.645
very far above my body.

43:04.816 --> 43:07.884
I saw the body laying there
and there were people around it,

43:07.919 --> 43:10.219
and I was still me,
I was still Krista,

43:10.255 --> 43:12.889
but I had no relationship
with anything that I

43:12.924 --> 43:15.224
was witnessing below.

43:15.260 --> 43:16.759
It’s happening but you're still

43:16.795 --> 43:18.094
not involved in it?

43:18.129 --> 43:19.896
Correct.

43:19.931 --> 43:22.031
I felt this tugging to my left,

43:22.067 --> 43:24.500
something kind of
pulled at me a little bit,

43:24.536 --> 43:27.003
as if to say, come on.

43:27.038 --> 43:30.106
And I, yes, okay, I’ll go.

43:30.141 --> 43:33.343
I just started moving.

43:33.645 --> 43:37.080
Through the wall and
into this bright white space

43:37.115 --> 43:39.349
that was just a flash.

43:39.384 --> 43:43.519
I came out into what
I called my Eden,

43:43.555 --> 43:46.623
it was a space that
was incredibly beautiful,

43:46.658 --> 43:50.760
green, rolling hills, beautiful,
blue sky, there was a deep,

43:50.795 --> 43:55.064
evergreen forest, and to my
left there was a moss covered,

43:55.100 --> 43:58.701
rock waterfall, and
it was beyond beautiful.

43:59.838 --> 44:02.171
I felt like I was at one with it and

44:02.207 --> 44:04.507
it was one with me.

44:04.542 --> 44:09.345
I was flanked on both sides
by what I refer to as my

44:09.381 --> 44:13.616
spiritual guides or what
we would call angels, here,

44:14.886 --> 44:19.122
they were very tall and thin
and almost like they were

44:19.157 --> 44:22.892
wearing drapes, and they
communicated to me that I

44:22.927 --> 44:26.529
could either stay in
that place, that Eden,

44:26.564 --> 44:30.466
I could move beyond
that to what came next,

44:30.502 --> 44:32.669
or I could come back here.

44:32.704 --> 44:36.439
And as soon as I
made that decision...

44:38.810 --> 44:41.678
I started to move backwards
very, very quickly,

44:41.713 --> 44:45.248
and they sort of turned to me
and communicated well if you

44:45.283 --> 44:50.319
choose to go back you need
to share what you learned here,

44:50.555 --> 44:53.956
and I had this feeling
of tremendous love

44:53.992 --> 44:57.860
just permeated me.

45:00.265 --> 45:01.798
Awesome.

45:01.833 --> 45:03.332
Yeah.

45:03.368 --> 45:04.934
As far as I can tell, you

45:04.969 --> 45:06.669
just described heaven.

45:06.705 --> 45:10.973
It was heaven, it was my heaven.

45:11.009 --> 45:13.342
When do you get back to the time that

45:13.378 --> 45:16.446
you know, oh, wow, okay,
I'm right back here.

45:16.481 --> 45:19.982
They were able to get
me back and awake

45:20.018 --> 45:24.387
on some level roughly
24 hours after the event,

45:24.422 --> 45:28.791
and I woke up that morning
just wanting to, you know,

45:28.827 --> 45:31.260
shout from the hilltops
what I had learned,

45:31.296 --> 45:33.963
what had happened to me.

45:33.998 --> 45:37.800
Religion, got one?

45:38.570 --> 45:41.504
My religion is love, you know...

45:41.539 --> 45:46.409
God, to me, is love.

45:46.578 --> 45:48.177
That’s what we were taught when we

45:48.213 --> 45:49.512
were three years old.

45:50.982 --> 45:54.951
God is love.

45:54.986 --> 45:56.753
And it's that simple.

45:56.788 --> 45:58.187
We are love.

45:58.223 --> 45:59.856
Now, hold on a second,

45:59.891 --> 46:05.461
you're gonna say to the entire
world it's as simple as that?

46:05.497 --> 46:07.697
For me it is.

46:07.732 --> 46:11.267
Well, I have to believe that it's

46:11.302 --> 46:15.071
as simple as that.

46:15.106 --> 46:17.073
Yeah.

46:17.108 --> 46:20.076
All of this we have discussed is

46:20.111 --> 46:24.947
around the birth or
attempted birth of a baby.

46:27.886 --> 46:29.719
Which is it?

46:29.754 --> 46:31.554
The birth of my daughter.

46:31.589 --> 46:33.289
So you have her?

46:33.324 --> 46:35.224
She is a reality?

46:35.260 --> 46:36.692
Would you like to meet her?

46:36.728 --> 46:37.994
Of course.

46:38.029 --> 46:40.763
Let’s go.

46:41.132 --> 46:42.131
Hey Maggie.

46:42.167 --> 46:43.933
Hi.

46:43.968 --> 46:45.468
There’s somebody I want you to meet.

46:45.503 --> 46:46.769
What are you doing?

46:46.805 --> 46:48.104
Nice to meet you.

46:48.139 --> 46:49.472
What?

46:49.507 --> 46:50.773
Don't I get a hug?

46:50.809 --> 46:52.074
Oh hi!

46:52.110 --> 46:54.911
Oh my goodness.

46:56.281 --> 46:59.215
Okay, alright, you know
we're here to talk to your mom

46:59.250 --> 47:01.384
about you'alls experience?

47:01.419 --> 47:02.819
Yeah.

47:02.854 --> 47:04.253
How do you feel?

47:04.289 --> 47:06.756
I was ten, 11, when
she first sat me down and

47:06.791 --> 47:09.058
talked to me about it,
and when I first heard about

47:09.093 --> 47:12.461
it I didn't really
understand it all that much.

47:12.497 --> 47:14.030
It went over my head.

47:14.065 --> 47:18.367
After that I was around 14
when I finally realized why

47:18.403 --> 47:21.270
she thinks so highly
of this experience,

47:21.306 --> 47:24.440
and I can finally
understand how to apply it

47:24.475 --> 47:25.908
to my own life.

47:25.944 --> 47:28.978
It makes sense
to me that at ten your mum

47:29.013 --> 47:32.481
explaining to you your birth,
that's about as far as you

47:32.517 --> 47:33.749
can go with it.

47:33.785 --> 47:35.318
Uh huh, yeah.

47:35.353 --> 47:37.119
Until things start to percolate

47:37.155 --> 47:38.287
Over the years.

47:38.323 --> 47:39.555
Yeah.

47:39.591 --> 47:44.794
Well Maggie, darling, I am so happy

47:44.829 --> 47:45.962
To see you.

47:45.997 --> 47:47.530
It’s such an honor.

47:47.565 --> 47:50.833
I mean, particularly
knowing mom and

47:50.869 --> 47:55.705
you and your trip together,
I am happy to see you here.

47:56.474 --> 48:00.009
Thank you so much.

48:01.746 --> 48:04.914
So many faiths have so many beliefs

48:04.949 --> 48:07.950
about heaven and hell.

48:07.986 --> 48:09.852
But Krista,

48:09.888 --> 48:14.290
like so many other survivors
of near death experiences,

48:14.325 --> 48:19.562
came back from her trip
with an overwhelming

48:19.597 --> 48:24.533
feeling of love, that's heaven.

48:26.504 --> 48:31.374
Heaven is simply love.

48:31.409 --> 48:34.610
And that's the power of
heaven and hell, I think.

48:34.812 --> 48:40.049
How they affect us emotionally
and fill us with love of our

48:40.084 --> 48:44.253
brothers and sisters and
fear that drives us away

48:44.289 --> 48:48.925
from evil and hope
for a brighter future.

48:51.095 --> 48:56.399
It drives us to make
a positive change,

48:57.535 --> 49:03.472
not in some other world
but right here on earth.

49:09.380 --> 49:13.149
My journey to understand
heaven and hell has taken me

49:13.184 --> 49:16.919
from the bowels of the
earth to the gates of Eden.

49:18.523 --> 49:22.191
From people who live in
the shadow of the inferno to

49:22.226 --> 49:26.062
those who bathe in the
light of paradise.

49:34.572 --> 49:37.640
Heaven and hell
are not just ideas.

49:37.675 --> 49:40.376
They're a part of us.

49:40.411 --> 49:43.946
A part of what we
yearn to escape.

